translated: Fraenckel, Gösta Josef, wholesaler, Gothenburg, born on 20/7/85 in Gothenburg to wholesaler Moritz F. and Amelie Bensow. Married for 13 years to Hervor Hjelt. Children: Bengt born in 1915, a Captain, Irma born in 1917, married to engineer Göran Hartzell, Berit born in 1921, married to Dr. Pelle Hell-dal, Karin born in 1923, student. Studied at Gothenburg High School, graduated in 1904. Studied abroad in Germany and France from 1906-1908, traveled to several European countries as well as North Africa and the USA. Second Lieutenant in the Gothenburg Artillery Regiment from 1906-1911 and Lieutenant from 1916-1919. Co-owner of firm Moritz Fraenckel & Co. in Gothenburg since 1909 and sole owner since 1911. Board member of Elektrokem. A-B, KAK, KSAK, and A^rokl. in Gothenburg, member of AA, Par Bricole, as well as around 100 other associations and clubs. Has written travelogues about Africa and Finland as well as articles in newspapers and magazines. Hobbies include cars and aviation. Awards received: GVrsJmt, RNO, KTunNI, RFinlVROlkl, TyskRKHt-2kl, KAKGM, Sv. Mosskult:fören. GM, Västg.-Dals skytteförb. GM, KSAKSM, KAK förarm. i guld, LLA 19. The abbreviation “\d\d m.” indicates the year of marriage.
